# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers per path.
#
# Last matching pattern wins. GitHub only enforces this when
# "Require review from Code Owners" is enabled on the protected branch
# (Settings → Branches → Branch protection rules).
#
# Replace the placeholders below with real GitHub handles before merging:
#   @LEAD   — repo owner / final reviewer on anything shared or risky
#   @DEV1   — Learn-focused dev
#   @DEV2   — Collect-focused dev
# If both devs float across products, see the bottom of this file.

# ── Default ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*                                   @LEAD

# ── Shared code (lead reviews — touches both products) ─────────────────
/client/src/features/shared/        @LEAD
/client/src/lib/                    @LEAD
/client/src/app/                    @LEAD
/client/src/config/                 @LEAD
/client/src/index.css               @LEAD
/server/src/lib/                    @LEAD
/server/src/middleware/             @LEAD
/server/src/config/                 @LEAD
/server/src/features/shared/        @LEAD

# ── Learn product ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/client/src/features/learn/         @LEAD @DEV1
/client/src/app/routes/learn/       @LEAD @DEV1
/server/src/features/learn/         @LEAD @DEV1

# ── Collect product ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/client/src/features/collect/       @LEAD @DEV2
/client/src/app/routes/collect/     @LEAD @DEV2
/server/src/features/collect/       @LEAD @DEV2

# ── Infra, deps, deploy config (lead-only) ─────────────────────────────
/.github/                           @LEAD
/CLAUDE.md                          @LEAD
/README.md                          @LEAD
**/package.json                     @LEAD
**/package-lock.json                @LEAD
**/tsconfig*.json                   @LEAD
**/vite.config.ts                   @LEAD
**/eslint.config.js                 @LEAD
/render.yaml                        @LEAD

# ── If both devs float across products ─────────────────────────────────
# Replace the product blocks above with a single block:
#
#   /client/src/features/learn/     @LEAD @DEV1 @DEV2
#   /client/src/features/collect/   @LEAD @DEV1 @DEV2
#   ...
#
# GitHub requires only one of the listed owners to approve, so this
# keeps both devs eligible reviewers without forcing both to sign off.
